President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Father Pius Pietrzyk to the Board of Directors of the Legal Services Corporation. Father Pius is currently studying at the Pontifical University of St. Thomas Aquinas in Rome and serving at the Basilica of San Clemente. He has been a member of the Board of Directors since 2010 and has previously worked as a pro bono attorney and an attorney at Sidley & Austin. Father Pius holds a B.A. from the University of Arizona, a J.D. from the University of Chicago, and S.T.B./M.Div. and S.T.L degrees from the Pontifical Faculty of the Immaculate Conception.